text.section:
The provisions of this subtitle shall be fully implemented according to the following schedule:
on or before July 1, 2003, full implementation by:
the Department of Human Resources;
the Department of Labor, Licensing, and Regulation;
the Department of Health and Mental Hygiene;
the Department of Juvenile Services; and
the Workers' Compensation Commission;
on or before July 1, 2004, full implementation by:
the Department of Aging;
the Department of Public Safety and Correctional Services;
the Department of Transportation, not including the Maryland Transit Administration;
the Commission on Civil Rights;
the Department of State Police; and
five independent agencies, boards, or commissions, to be determined by the Secretary of Human Resources, in consultation with the Office of the Attorney General;
on or before July 1, 2005, full implementation by:
the Comptroller of Maryland;
the Department of Housing and Community Development;
the Maryland Transit Administration;
the Department of Natural Resources;
the Maryland State Department of Education;
the Office of the Attorney General; and
five independent agencies, boards, or commissions to be determined by the Secretary of Human Resources, in consultation with the Office of the Attorney General; and
on or before July 1, 2006, full implementation by:
the Department of Agriculture;
the Department of Business and Economic Development;
the Department of Veterans Affairs;
the Department of the Environment; and
five independent agencies, boards, or commissions to be determined by the Secretary of Human Resources, in consultation with the Office of the Attorney General.
